<div id="right">
    <div class="padding">
      <h1>Research & Development</h1>
      <p class="path"> <a href="/en/VaV/">Research</a>
</p>
 <!-- Content -->
<div id="ocms_35035" class="ocms_de_norm">
<p>In  the following years, mainly related to the emerge of new activities of  RD&amp;I projects, a significant deluge of experimental data is  expected, produced by new digital instruments (e.g., modern genome  sequencers produce TBs of data in a single experiment). In order to  store, access, and process the data, nowadays methods will no longer be  sufficient. It will be necessary to develop new and/or modify known  algorithms in order to efficiently use the multi-core computation  environment. The common requirement of data confidentiality asks for new  ways in security, user authentication and access to data, computations  and their results. Deploying potential of such environments will no  longer be possible without tight cooperation among informaticians and  application field experts, having impact also in education on both  sides.</p>
<h2><strong>Cooperation with research groups (by means of common projects)</strong></h2>
<p>CERIT-SC users do not act only as service consumers, but mainly as  partners in research and production application of its results. Groups  of employees and CERIT-SC students together with members of other  institutions will be formed, working on specific problems of user  communities that require non-trivial e-infrastructure support. The  topics will be, e.g., paralelisation, new computation methods, computer  modeling and simulation, huge data manipulation, etc.</p>
<ul>
    <li>Global climate change</li>
    <li>Biobanka klinických vzorků</li>
    <li>Modely šíření epileptického záchvatu a dalších dějů v mozku</li>
    <li>Virtual mikroskop, patological atlases</li>
    <li>Modelování molekul a biochemické výpočty</li>
    <li>Analýza mikroskopických obrazů buněčných kultur</li>
    <li>Analýza výstupních dat hmotnostního spektrometru</li>
    <li>Hvězdný vítr, fotometrické a astrometrické vlastnosti hvězd</li>
    <li>Bioinformatické databáze</li>
</ul>
<h2><strong>Research and development in the area of flexible infrastructures</strong>&nbsp;</h2>
<p>Research and development activites of the centre are oriented into  areas related to operating the computation equipment installed in the  centre. Main target areas include planning (virtual clusters,  preemption, etc.), grid and cloud systems, security (authentisation,  atuhorisation, federations), data processing, etc.</p>
<ul>
    <li>Security</li>
    <li>Clouds</li>
    <li>Prostředí pro spolupráci</li>
    <li>Optimalization tools &amp; GPU</li>
    <li>Planning<strong><br />
    </strong></li>
</ul>
<h3>Students work</h3>
<p>Centre CERIT-SC tightly cooperates with the Faculty of Informatics as  well as other parts of the Masaryk University. It targets specifically  into integrating master and graduate students. PhD study consultants  work in the centre, helping students to integrade tightly into relevant  research areas, their results immediately applied in the centre itself  as well as other places. Integration into national and international  projects and obtaining experience working in international project teams  is obviously included.</p>
<p>The Centre offers cooperation in mainly PhD  student growth in other areas that are significant e-infrastructure  users (usually in the form of block courses and/or semester lectures).</p>
</div>
